rows.title: Player Vs Player CYOA
rows.imageSourceTooltip: One Piece colored panel: By Greiish

rows.title: Player Information
rows.titleText: Information on some things that both Players get.

objects.title: Player's Body
objects.text:
Grants your body the physical abilities of a player. 
Or really, just gamer's body but renamed.
You heal to max health upon sleeping a full night.
You use HP to determine whether you live or die.
You no longer expel waste.

objects.title: Player's Mind
objects.text:
Depending on your alignment, this is either Hero Player's Mind or Villain Player's Mind.
This is designed to ensure that you stick to your chosen side. Or, at the very least, your heroic or villainous ideals throughout the duration of the game.
Additionally, it gives you the backbone to actually fight.

objects.title: Limited System
objects.text:
You have a system, but in the interests of the game, you are capped out at a certain point. Don't worry though, you'll be at the top of your verse by the time you're at that level.
This system has an inventory, crafting system, the ability to create your own skills/spells, achievements, help menu, and a gacha system for that extra dose of randomness.

objects.title: Instant Dungeons
objects.text:
Once per week, you can go through an instant dungeon.

Once you hit level 20, you can queue for co-op dungeons, taking 4 other players of the same alignment through a dungeon together.

objects.title: 1 Year
objects.text:
You have 1 year to, at the very least, meet the other player.
If you cannot do so, your match will be terminated.
After meeting your antagonist, the match may continue on for however long it requires.

objects.title: Basic Rules
objects.text:
You must personally kill the other player, or at least just show up to the final battle. This rule does not apply when the other player gets killed from his own fault.
Do not fraternize with the other player. You may have conversations with them but don't agree to spare each other or make a deal concerning who wins.

rows.title: Players
rows.titleText:
Now, who are the players?

"You" refers to you, filling out this CYOA.
"Real Person" refers to someone real in this world, whether it's someone you know or a celebrity.
"Character" refers to any fictional character, original or from somewhere else.

rows.title: Protaganist
rows.titleText:
Who is the "protagonist" of this match? 
Or, really, just player 1.

objects.title: You
objects.text: You, the person filling out this CYOA.

objects.title: Character
objects.text: An character from any media or your daydreams take the stage.

objects.title: Real Person
objects.text: A real person you know.

objects.title: You
objects.text:
You're now the antagonist.
If you're already the protagonist, this can be a clone of you.

objects.title: Character
objects.text: Can be both real, or from your own head.

objects.title: Real Person
objects.text: If you have someone you don't like, this would be a great place to put them.

objects.title: CYOA
objects.text: The Protagonist played this CYOA, making all the choices, fully aware of it.

objects.title: Antagonist CYOA
objects.text: The Antagonist played this CYOA, making all of the choices, fully aware.

objects.title: Both Played The CYOA
objects.text: Both the Protagonist and Antagonist played the CYOA with each other.

objects.title: No CYOA
objects.text: Both players found themselves transported away by any means you want, stuck in this match.

rows.title: Difficulty
rows.titleText: Now, how hard do you want your match to be?

objects.title: Ez
objects.text: Ya good

objects.title: Mid
objects.text: Da lean

objects.title: Hard
objects.text: jar

objects.title: Difficult
objects.text: Clownery.

rows.title: World
rows.titleText: Explanation for why I'm skimping out. The scarier the world, the more points the two players get.

objects.title: Basically Earth
objects.text: Basically earth. Low risk low reward.

objects.title: Fantasy
objects.text: Easy mode.

objects.title: Default
objects.text: So, your world is 50/50.

objects.title: Hard
objects.text: The world is fairly unfair.

objects.title: Uwah, scary.
objects.text: Anything else that I don't feel like listing. Super hard stuff.

objects.title: Hero
objects.text:
You choose to walk the path of a hero.
This ensures that, for the duration of this match, you will be aligned with the good guys.
The Enemy Player will be aligned with the forces of evil.

objects.title: Villain
objects.text:
You choose to walk the path of a villain.
This ensures that, for the duration of this match, you will be aligned with the bad guys.
The Enemy Player will be aligned with the forces of good.

objects.title: Human
objects.text: Humany human human

objects.title: Elf
objects.text: Elfy elf elf

objects.title: Dwarf
objects.text: Dwarfy dwarf dwarf

objects.title: Other
objects.text: We'll just trust that you have a good idea in mind. Can't be too overpowered, though.

rows.title: Class
rows.titleText:
Pick 2
These classes are very specific. If you choose a custom class, it should be fairly specific as well.
Combining classes means you can combine the two spells/skills into one. For example pyromancers and priests can use holy flames on all of their attacks.

objects.title: Swordsman
objects.text: All swords.

objects.title: Polearm Warrior
objects.text: Anything with a long stick.

objects.title: Brawler
objects.text: Specifically them hands.

objects.title: Kicker
objects.text: Specifically them Legs.

objects.title: Commander
objects.text: Buff others.

objects.title: Archer
objects.text: Specifically the bow.

objects.title: Ranger
objects.text: Specifically the gun.

objects.title: Psychic
objects.text: Mostly the telekinesis kind and not much of the mind reading kind.

objects.title: Summoner
objects.text: Pick an archetype like humans/beasts/angels/demons or whatever. You are now an expert in summoning them.

objects.title: Other
objects.text: We'll trust that you have a good idea. Can't be too overpowered, though. Keep it simple.

objects.title: Stronger Body
objects.text: Your body is now stronger. Bonus to all of your physical stats.

objects.title: Ageless
objects.text:
You no longer age.
Of course, most gamers get this fairly early on in their adventures anyways, but maybe you need the resistance to aging magic.

objects.title: Extra Time
objects.text: Instead of requiring to find your enemy in 1 year, you now get 2.

objects.title: Charisma
objects.text: Doesn't completely change your character.

objects.title: Battle Ready
objects.text: Basic knowledge of how to fight. Everything else you will have to earn through trial and error.

objects.title: Destructive
objects.text:
Your attacks will do more damage to the surrounding area, essentially giving you AoE on all of your attacks.
Hope you don't have to pay for property damage.

objects.title: 3rd Class Slot
objects.text: Did you want a 3rd class slot? Go and get it!

objects.title: Hybrid Race
objects.text:
Get a second race.
Benefits & negatives cancel each other out.

objects.title: Another Profession
objects.text: Get another profession.

objects.title: Faster Leveling
objects.text: If you want the simplest way to get stronger than your opponent, this is it.

objects.title: Intellect
objects.text: This won't completely change your character, but it should help shore up your weak points.

objects.title: Faster Regen
objects.text: Gamer's Body already helps with this, but maybe you want more.

objects.title: Sleepless
objects.text: No longer need sleep

objects.title: 2 Weekly Dungeons
objects.text: You can now create 2 IDs per week.

objects.title: Loyal Henchmen
objects.text: People will flock to your cause.

objects.title: Co-Op
objects.text: Bring a friend with you! They're the lesser partner, though, and cannot choose anything beyond their race, classes, and professions.

objects.title: Subscription to Lord Sangemah Bay
objects.text:
Occasionally, Lord Sangemah Bay, Dori, will arrive to your location, offering her wares for money, items, or favors.
It just so happens that those wares are often things that you really require at that moment.
Do be warned, she is a long-standing member of Fair and Balanced Incorporated. You will not win a fight against her. Nothing will.

objects.title: Developer Assistance
objects.text:
You can have one of the developers of this game stay in your head for the duration of the game!
Of course, this isn't always a bonus. It really depends on which developer you get.
Still, if you need help, they will always be ready to backseat everything you do.

If you chose this option, go to this google document and roll a random number.
https://docs.google.com/document/d/1fmZ959B2iY59AKe-Fva1j2R2F5ocABa7jJnjVVmByqg/edit?usp=sharing

objects.title: Invisible Signals
objects.text:
Normally, when using a skill or spell, you would at the very least point a hand or instrument towards the desired location.
Now this isn't necessary. You just have to will it to happen.

objects.title: Phone a Friend
objects.text:
Once a week, you can phone someone from back home to help you walk through something.
Need to look up something? Ask your friend who's a superfan of the series. Want to tell your mom and dad you love them? Feel free. Need advice on how to kick someone's ass? I'm sure you've got a friend for that.

objects.title: Strategist
objects.text:
You're capable of making a plan and sticking with it.
This also increases your natural aptitude for making plans, yes.

objects.title: It works like that.
objects.text:
You don't know how many times a prospective Gamer has tried something, only to be met with the cold, harsh reality of "That spell, ability, or item doesn't work like that."
Now, most things will work as they do in your head.

objects.title: Fodder go away
objects.text: Sometimes, you just want to get to the big bad guy. With this perk, all of the fodder in-between you and the big bad will suddenly be preoccupied with something else.

objects.title: Fair 1v1
objects.text: Nobody will interrupt your 1v1

objects.title: Natural Talent
objects.text: You have the experience of control of someone practicing their ability for about a month.

objects.title: Dramatic
objects.text: You like to listen to your own voice.

objects.title: No Gamer's Body
objects.text: You no longer have access to Gamer's Body

objects.title: No Gamer's Mind
objects.text: You no longer have access to Gamer's Mind

objects.title: Frail
objects.text: Your body is frail and lacks physicality.

objects.title: Manaless
objects.text: You have no mana. Literally 0.

objects.title: Odd Weapon Choices
objects.text: Your weapon of choice cannot be normal. If someone goes, "Oh, I can see someone using that as a weapon" you are doing it wrong.

objects.title: Masked
objects.text: You have to keep a full mask over your face at all times. If you lose it for too long, you'll be extremely paranoid and retreat immediately.

objects.title: Pyrovision
objects.text: The world isn't what it seems to be...

objects.title: Gambling Addiction
objects.text:
When given a risky option, you are inclined to take the riskiest option for the greatest reward.
Doesn't make you stupid. Just bold and reckless.

objects.title: Garbage stat
objects.text: Pick one stat. That stat is now permanently at 0.

objects.title: Solo Fighter
objects.text: No matter your plans, you tend to be separated into fighting alone.

objects.title: Curse of Conflict
objects.text:
Every single fight that you will have will be at least high-diff. There will be no easy fights for you, not even against the fodder of the world.
Sink or swim. If you can overcome all of your enemies, you will be more than prepared to take on the enemy player.
This drawback does not work on the enemy player.

objects.title: Styleless
objects.text:
Imagine the average isekai protagonist with their basic t-shirt or track suit if they're bold.
That'll be you for your entire match.

objects.title: Subscription to Lady Bonajade
objects.text:
At your darkest moments, Lady Bonajade will be there to offer you a deal to help you escape your situation and fulfill your desires.
These deals are heavily in her favor, and the price might be too heavy to bear. Do not worry, though. It is worth the price.
Do be warned, very few of her customers are able to bloom into fully grown Gamers. 
If you try going back on your deal, it will not end very well for you.

objects.title: Voices
objects.text:
Every single sentient being you kill will have their souls stuck inside your head.
They can speak.

objects.title: Clueless
objects.text:
Which world are you going to? Did you have a plan or a reason why you're going to that world?
Well, now you don't remember anything about that world.

objects.title: Named After Fair and Balanced Incorporated
objects.text:
Everything you name has to be named after one of our esteemed members of Fair and Balanced Incorporated.
See, the thing is, we're not going to give you the list of names until after you drop into your world.
Now, we're a company filled with people whose names are derived from their gamer tags of old. Do you want to take a chance with that?
This is the google document with the names on it.
https://docs.google.com/document/d/1fmZ959B2iY59AKe-Fva1j2R2F5ocABa7jJnjVVmByqg/edit?usp=sharing

objects.title: Seven Deadly Sins
objects.text:
Pick one of the Seven Deadly Sins. You are now afflicted by a curse from one of those sins.
Yes, it will be worse than what you're expecting.

objects.title: Sound Stupid
objects.text:
If you pick this option, you will sound stupid. In voice, in your choice of words, in everything.
This will probably help make people underestimate you.

objects.title: Specific Weakness
objects.text:
Pick something that you have a decent shot at coming across in your chosen world. Like, silver or maybe poison attacks.
You are now especially weak to it.

objects.title: Announcement
objects.text: You have to shout the name of all of your attacks before you can actually use them.

objects.title: Cast Out
objects.text: Through one reason or another, your people have abandoned you. You are alone.

objects.title: Ugly
objects.text: You look ugly. People might think that you have a terrible disease or something.

objects.title: The Worst Option Possible
objects.text:
Once a month, you have to choose to make the worst decision you could possibly make in that moment.
We will let you decide. If you don't figure it out by the end of the month, we will decide it for you.

objects.title: Unfamiliar Body
objects.text:
Your body is probably different than what it was before, yeah?
In our initial launch of the PvP program, we didn't actually let people have automatic control over their new bodies and had to learn everything themselves.
It was fine, but one guy, Zavvox, took 24 whole hours to get used to his body, so we ended up letting everyone have a freebie.
You will not.

objects.title: Weapon
objects.text: A weapon for your classes.

objects.title: High Grade Weapon
objects.text: A good weapon for your classes. You might even be able to get away with using this one weapon for your entire game.

objects.title: Gacha Token
objects.text: Gacha token

objects.title: All Cutting Knife
objects.text: This knife can cut literally anything. Good luck getting in melee reach with the distance of this knife, though.

objects.title: Supersuit
objects.text:
An outfit tailored specifically for you.
If it breaks, it will repair itself and be placed into your inventory.

objects.title: Property
objects.text: You now own property which you can stay at.

objects.title: Cash
objects.text: If you need money, this will place a sizable sum of money into your inventory.

objects.title: Ship
objects.text:
You get a ship.
You do not get the knowledge of how to sail a ship.

objects.title: Airplane
objects.text:
You get an airplane.
You do not get the knowledge of how to fly an airplane.

objects.title: Player Compass
objects.text: A compass that will always point in the direction of the enemy player.

objects.title: Treasure Map
objects.text: Leads to treasure that will be worth your time.

objects.title: Legal Documents
objects.text: You are a drop in. But with this, you can convince people you've always been there.

objects.title: Phone
objects.text:
It's a phone.
It may or may not have internet.

objects.title: Art Supplies
objects.text: Art supplies if you need it for, say, a mission.

objects.title: Cooking Supplies
objects.text: Cooking supplies that can be put down anywhere. You can go a month with just this.

objects.title: Developer Notes
objects.text:
A book filled with a bunch of random stuff put in by some of the developers.
Is it actually useful? It's a 50/50.

objects.title: Binding Chains
objects.text: When chaining someone, they cannot escape unless they are another Gamer.

objects.title: Lasso of Truth
objects.text:
Forces people to tell the truth.
Not very durable.

objects.title: Crash Course to Fighting
objects.text: A book written by the masters of fighting. Will last you for the entire match.

objects.title: Copium
objects.text: If something bad happens to you, a dose of copium will make it feel all right.

objects.title: Armor
objects.text: Basic armor for your class.

objects.title: High Grade Armor
objects.text: A good set of armor for your classes. You might even be able to get away with using this one weapon for your entire game.

objects.title: Gym Equipment
objects.text: An entire gym's worth of equipment placed into your inventory. Good for training and raising your physical attributes.

objects.title: Library Books
objects.text:
An entire library's worth of books placed into your inventory. Good for training and raising your intellectual and magical attributes.
Yes, this library will contain books relevant to your world.

objects.title: Piercing Glasses
objects.text: If there's something you cannot usually see in your world, these glasses will let you see them.

objects.title: Simple nowhere
objects.text: Easy, own pace.

objects.title: Side Area
objects.text: Medium, one of the less known places.

objects.title: Main City
objects.text: Easy, in main city.

objects.title: Protagonist's lair
objects.text: Very easy, with your buds.

objects.title: Antagonist's lair
objects.text: Hard. You are in the middle of something bad.

rows.title: Missions
rows.titleText: If you pick these missions, you MUST complete them before killing your enemy player.

objects.title: Worldwide Recognition
objects.text:
Be recognized throughout the world.
Obviously much more easier in a modern setting.

objects.title: Fate of The World
objects.text: Tell the world about this match- And make them believe it.

objects.title: Level 150
objects.text:
Most players end their match far before they hit level 150.
However, now you will be part of that small group who have reached the ceiling placed upon you.
(This may take a full year.)

objects.title: Achievement Hunter
objects.text: Obtain 100 achievements

objects.title: Paragon
objects.text: Depending on your alignment, save 1,000 people or kill 1,000 people.

objects.title: Work of Art
objects.text:
Write and publish a book, paint a gallery of paintings, or sing an album.
Should attract some attention.

objects.title: End of the Old Order
objects.text:
That government they had? Take it down.
The crime ring that's been there for centuries? The buck stops with you.

objects.title: End of The Journey
objects.text:
Reach the place that all adventurers aspire to one day reach in your world.
For example, on Earth, Mount Everest.
One Piece, Laugh Tale.
Many Isekais, The Demon King's Castle.

objects.title: Epithet
objects.text: Gain an epithet by the people. You cannot try and convince people to call you something.

objects.title: Near Death Experience
objects.text:
Reach 1 HP in real combat.
Good luck.

rows.title: Enemy Creator
rows.titleText: Now, the creation of your Enemy.

objects.text: Humany human human

objects.title: Elf
objects.text: Elfy elf elf

objects.title: Dwarf
objects.text: Dwarfy dwarf dwarf

objects.title: Other
objects.text: We'll just trust that you have a good idea in mind. Can't be too overpowered, though.

objects.text: Easy, own pace.

objects.title: Side Area
objects.text: Medium, one of the less known places.

objects.title: Main City
objects.text: Easy, in main city.

objects.title: Protagonist's lair
objects.text: Very easy, with your buds.

objects.title: Antagonist's lair
objects.text: Hard. You are in the middle of something bad.

defaultRowText: This is a row, and inside of it, you can place choices. On both rows and choices Requirements can be placed, which will block a row from being viewed, or make the player unable to select a choice, depending on either Point-types or the Ids of other choices. Point-types can be made in Features then Manage Points. Hovering over buttons will explain what they do. The Design of the project can be changed in 'Modify Design' at the side navigation bar, and private styling for each row can be turned on in the rows Settings. Default text like this can be turned off in Features -> Manage Defaults.
defaultChoiceText: This is a Choice, and inside of it, you can place images and text. Scores can be added to it, and have Point-types attached. Addons can be added underneath the image and text. In the Functions at the bottom of the choice, there is an array of different things that can be done. Default text like this can be turned off in Features then Manage Defaults.
